## Execution Timeline

```
Start
  ↓
  ├─→ Stage 1 (Infrastructure) [Concurrent]
  │   ├─→ authenticate()
  │   ├─→ connect WebSocket ✓
  │   ├─→ fetch markets from API
  │   └─→ initialize DuckDB database ✓
  │
  ├─→ Stage 2 (Market Making) [Concurrent]
  │   ├─→ Wait 5s for feed to populate
  │   ├─→ Select top 5-10 markets
  │   ├─→ Every 30s:
  │   │   ├─→ Get latest orderbook
  │   │   ├─→ Compute quotes (Avellaneda-Stoikov)
  │   │   ├─→ Check inventory limits ✓
  │   │   └─→ Place/update orders (TODO: implement)
  │   └─→ Track fills and P&L
  │
  ├─→ Stage 3 (Arbitrage) [Concurrent, TODO]
  │   ├─→ Every 5s:
  │   │   ├─→ Build market relationship graph
  │   │   ├─→ Scan baskets for overpricing
  │   │   ├─→ Scan parent-child for mispricings
  │   │   ├─→ Calculate net edge (fee-adjusted)
  │   │   └─→ Execute if edge > threshold (TODO)
  │   └─→ Track arbitrage fills
  │
  └─→ Monitoring [Every 60s]
      ├─→ Log portfolio state
      ├─→ Check daily P&L limits
      ├─→ Report metrics to Telegram (optional)
      └─→ Update database
```

