## Strategy Hierarchy

```
Market Making (Primary)
├─ Always-on quotes
├─ Earns spread + rebates
├─ No prediction needed
├─ 78-85% win rate
└─ $500-2000 typical profit/month

    └─→ Basket Arbitrage (Secondary)
        ├─ Detects overpriced/underpriced baskets
        ├─ Parent-child relationships
        ├─ Requires prediction
        ├─ 70-80% win rate
        └─ $1000-5000 typical profit/month

            └─→ AI Probability Arb (Tertiary, TODO)
                ├─ News-driven pricing inefficiency
                ├─ LLM ensemble probability
                ├─ 30-second edge windows
                ├─ 65-75% win rate
                └─ $3000-8000 typical profit/month

                    └─→ Advanced (Future)
                        ├─ Cross-venue arb (Kalshi ↔ Polymarket)
                        ├─ Leverage optimized
                        ├─ ML event prediction
                        └─ Institutional-grade infrastructure
```

